ABUJA (SundiataPost) – Nigeria’s COVID-19 infections continue to increase at an alarming rate, according to update released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Saturday night.Nigeria now has 12,233 confirmed cases.However, one important development is that the number of infections in Lagos reduced while there seems to be an upsurge in the  South-Eastern states of Ebonyi (23), Anambra (17) and Imo (12). Also worrisome is Rivers State (24) along with Edo (23). These are states where the infection rate had previously remained very low.The full report is as follows: Lagos-66FCT-50Delta-32Oyo-31Borno-26Rivers-24Edo-23Ebonyi-23Anambra-17Gombe-17Nasarawa-14Imo-12Kano-12Sokoto-12Jigawa-8Ogun-7Bauchi-5Kebbi-2Kaduna-2Katsina-2Ondo-2Abia-1Niger-1 12233 cases of #COVID19Discharged: 3826Deaths: 342 See state by state breakdown below: ABUJA - For the first time since the outbreak of the coronavirus pandemic in Nigeria, Kano has recorded the highest infection in a single day as reported by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Monday night. Kano had 23 new confirmed cases on Monday. In Lagos, which has… April 21, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA (SundiataPost) – Lagos, Nigeria’s economic powerhouse and epicentre of the Coronavirus pandemic on Saturday reported an all-time high record of 378 new COVID-19 infections. This is the highest daily report, so far, of new confirmed cases since the index case in February in Lagos. 52 in the FCT, 23… May 31, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - Nigeria's exposure to the COVID-19 pandemic is steadily moving towards alarming proportion as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported 86 new infections late Sunday night.This brought Nigeria's total confirmed cases to 627. The full report is as follows: Eighty-six new cases of #COVID19 have been reported;… April 20, 2020 In "Top Stories"